Legacy mode is actually a Joomla! system plugin. It allows you to use extensions that were written for Joomla! 1.0.x (and even Mambo) in you 1.5 site. It is a part of the core distribution of Joomla!, but it is disabled by default. It is said to offer over 90%...&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/docman/~4/231128050" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><feedburner:origLink>http://blog.joomlatools.org/2007/12/joomla-15rc4-memory-usage-and-legacy.html</feedburner:origLink></item><item><title>DOCman - Category versus document permissions</title><link>http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/docman/~3/231128051/joomla-docman-category-vs-document.html</link><category>tips'n'tricks</category><category>docman</category><category>mathias</category><category>optimization</category><author>noreply@blogger.com (Mathias Verraes)</author><pubDate>Sat, 06 Sep 2008 12:16:46 -0500</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-9202268460760907948.post-2565526519702963233</guid><app:edited xmlns:app="http://purl.org/atom/app#">2008-09-06T19:16:46.531+02:00</app:edited><thr:total xmlns:thr="http://purl.org/syndication/thread/1.0">0</thr:total><description>There's been a lot of confusion lately about category permissions in DOCman. Many people are trying to use categories in the same way they are using documents. Let me try to clear up the misunderstanding.
